    "ragtruth_id": "289",
    "text": "Cynthia Lennon, the first wife of John Lennon, passed away at the age of 75 after battling cancer. She was married to John Lennon from 1962 to 1968 and they had a son, Julian Lennon, together. Cynthia was a stabilizing force for John, who had lost his mother at a young age. However, their marriage faced challenges due to John's overwhelming fame and his relationship with Yoko Ono. Cynthia went on to write two books about her marriage to John and had no contact with the surviving members of the Beatles until 2006. Despite the difficulties, Cynthia described her life with John as amazing and wonderful. She is survived by her son, Julian.",
